<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="95.[151,1437,435,1182]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,651,677]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Distribution</emphasis>
. Europe, through Siberia to the Russian Far East (Kamchatka Kraj, Primorskij Kraj, Sakhalin, northern Kuriles), North and 
<collectingCountry box="[479,619,687,714]" name="South Korea" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">South Korea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[674,738,688,714]" name="Japan" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[752,867,687,713]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, southern Kuriles, Honshu, Kyushu).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
